&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dual role Receptionist / General Clinical Administrator &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;28 Hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen a Part-time&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; Receptionist/General Administrator &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;within the Antenatal Service, in Fetal and Maternal Medicine. Based across both City hospital campus and QMC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be committed to a high standard of patient care and safety. You will have a flexible attitude to work and be able to work as part of a multidisciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have good organisational skills and be able to manage your workload effectively. It is essential for you to be competent in using computer systems as you will be trained to use Medway PAS and Medway Maternity and other hospital systems appropriate to the role. We require good communication skills and an excellent telephone manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Professionalism is expected within this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have a good command of the English language with the ability to understand and accurately convey verbal and written information and you must be well motivated and reliable, with a “can do” attitude. Due to the sensitivity of the role you will need to be able to demonstrate a clear understanding of confidentiality issues. The ability to manage your time and prioritise your workload whilst remaining patient focused is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kirsty Cooper&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Administration Manager kirsty.cooper@nuh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01159691169 ex 55188&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that if you apply for a position with this Trust, you will be contacted via our candidate portal or via email. This includes invites for job interviews. We therefore recommend that you regularly check your candidate portal and email accounts&lt;/p&gt;
